    <h1>Emotion Detection in Healthcare: IEEE Journal Paper</h1>
    
    <div class="paper-info">
        <h2>Phanikumar Akkenapalli</h2>
        <p><strong>Department of Computer Science</strong><br>
        Rivier University, Nashua, New Hampshire<br>
        pakkenapalli@rivier.edu</p>
    </div>

    <img src="pha.jpg" alt="IEEE Research Paper - Emotion Detection in Healthcare">

    <p><strong>Abstract:</strong> This IEEE journal paper presents a multimodal emotion detection system achieving 91.5% accuracy by integrating facial expressions, speech analysis, and physiological signals (EEG, heart rate) for healthcare applications. The system uses ResNet-50/VGG-16 for facial analysis, Bi-LSTM/Transformers for speech, and 1D CNN/Bi-LSTM for physiological data across FER-2013, DEAP, IEMOCAP, HUME-Vid, and PhysioNet datasets.</p>


